{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779191438946,"sessionID":"ses_1bff4e2c5ffelBqOnmJS1wuf2p","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_00_FqAxAnFQzMIWei1f56o10265","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/react/docs/auth-guards.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/react/docs/auth-guards.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Authentication Guards\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: Route protection using 3 separate guard components and layout-level RBAC. Guards enforce authentication and role-based access control across route trees.\n6: \n7: > **Important:** The specific auth method (httpOnly cookies, Bearer tokens, sessions) and role names come from your project's PRD. This guide covers the structural patterns only.\n8: \n9: ---\n10: \n11: ## Role Contract (CRITICAL)\n12: \n13: Your auth system MUST be internally consistent about the type of `role` on the user object:\n14: \n15: - **Either** role is always a `number` (recommended for numeric enums), OR\n16: - role is always a `string` (recommended for string enums)\n17: \n18: **Never mix.** The JWT payload, the `/auth/login` response, the `/users/me` response, and the frontend `AuthUser` type must all agree. If they don't, `allowedRoles.includes(user.role)` fails silently and guards become permissive — a low-privilege user ends up able to view admin pages because `\"1\" !== 1` (or vice versa).\n19: \n20: Signs of role-type drift:\n21: - UI login for one role redirects to `/` (generic home) instead of the role-specific home\n22: - Chaos tests for role-gate protection fail intermittently\n23: - Guards render a flash of admin content before redirecting\n24: \n25: If you suspect drift in an existing project, the guards in this doc already normalize both sides via `String(...)` — but the better fix is at the backend JWT strategy. See `.claude/{$BACKEND}/guides/authentication-cookies.md` → \"Role coercion\".\n26: \n27: ---\n28: \n29: ## Guard Components\n30: \n31: ### 1. GuestGuard\n32: \n33: Protects auth pages (login, signup) — redirects authenticated users to their home route.\n34: \n35: Location: `~/components/guards/GuestGuard.tsx`\n36: \n37: ```typescript\n38: import { Navigate, Outlet } from 'react-router';\n39: import { useAuth } from '~/hooks/useAuth';\n40: import { Loader2 } from 'lucide-react';\n41: \n42: export function GuestGuard() {\n43:   const { isAuthenticated, authChecked } = useAuth();\n44: \n45:   if (!authChecked) {\n46:     return (\n47:       <div className=\"flex items-center justify-center h-screen\">\n48:         <Loader2 className=\"h-8 w-8 animate-spin text-muted-foreground\" />\n49:       </div>\n50:     );\n51:   }\n52: \n53:   if (isAuthenticated) {\n54:     return <Navigate to=\"/dashboard\" replace />;\n55:   }\n56: \n57:   return <Outlet />;\n58: }\n59: ```\n60: \n61: > GuestGuard renders `<Outlet />` (not `children`) because it is used as a **layout component** in the route config via `layout('pages/auth/layout.tsx', authRoutes)`.\n62: \n63: ### 2. AuthGuard\n64: \n65: Protects private routes — redirects unauthenticated users to login. Use for one-off component-level checks when inline RBAC in the layout isn't sufficient.\n66: \n67: Location: `~/components/guards/AuthGuard.tsx`\n68: \n69: ```typescript\n70: import { Navigate, Outlet } from 'react-router';\n71: import { useAuth } from '~/hooks/useAuth';\n72: import { Loader2 } from 'lucide-react';\n73: \n74: export function AuthGuard({ children }: { children?: React.ReactNode }) {\n75:   const { isAuthenticated, authChecked } = useAuth();\n76: \n77:   if (!authChecked) {\n78:     return (\n79:       <div className=\"flex items-center justify-center h-screen\">\n80:         <Loader2 className=\"h-8 w-8 animate-spin text-muted-foreground\" />\n81:       </div>\n82:     );\n83:   }\n84: \n85:   if (!isAuthenticated) {\n86:     return <Navigate to=\"/login\" replace />;\n87:   }\n88: \n89:   return children ? <>{children}</> : <Outlet />;\n90: }\n91: ```\n92: \n93: ### 3. RoleGuard\n94: \n95: Checks if user has one of the allowed roles — redirects to `/unauthorized` if not. Use for component-level role checks within a page.\n96: \n97: Location: `~/components/guards/RoleGuard.tsx`\n98: \n99: ```typescript\n100: import { Navigate, Outlet } from 'react-router';\n101: import { useAuth } from '~/hooks/useAuth';\n102: \n103: interface RoleGuardProps {\n104:   // Use a union of your project's Role enum values (numeric or string — be consistent)\n105:   allowedRoles: Array<string | number>;\n106:   children?: React.ReactNode;\n107: }\n108: \n109: export function RoleGuard({ allowedRoles, children }: RoleGuardProps) {\n110:   const { user, isAuthenticated } = useAuth();\n111: \n112:   if (!isAuthenticated || !user) {\n113:     return <Navigate to=\"/login\" replace />;\n114:   }\n115: \n116:   // Normalize both sides to string so number-vs-string role contracts don't silently fail.\n117:   // See \"Role Contract\" section above.\n118:   const allowed = allowedRoles.map(String).includes(String(user.role));\n119:   if (!allowed) {\n120:     return <Navigate to=\"/unauthorized\" replace />;\n121:   }\n122: \n123:   return children ? <>{children}</> : <Outlet />;\n124: }\n125: ```\n126: \n127: ---\n128: \n129: ## Guard Props Summary\n130: \n131: | Guard | Props | Purpose |\n132: |-------|-------|---------|\n133: | `GuestGuard` | none (renders `<Outlet />`) | Auth pages only — redirects logged-in users |\n134: | `AuthGuard` | `{ children?: ReactNode }` | Protected pages — redirects unauthenticated users |\n135: | `RoleGuard` | `{ allowedRoles: string[], children?: ReactNode }` | Role-specific — redirects wrong role to `/unauthorized` |\n136: \n137: ---\n138: \n139: ## Layout-Level Protection Pattern (Recommended)\n140: \n141: The recommended pattern is to **inline auth + RBAC checks directly in the layout component**, rather than wrapping layouts with guards. This gives the layout full control over loading states, redirects, and UI.\n142: \n143: ### Protected Layout with Inline RBAC\n144: \n145: ```typescript\n146: // ~/components/layouts/ProtectedLayout.tsx\n147: import { Outlet, Navigate, useLocation } from 'react-router';\n148: import { useAuth } from '~/hooks/useAuth';\n149: import { Sidebar } from '~/components/layout/Sidebar';\n150: import Header from '~/components/layout/Header';\n151: import { Loader2 } from 'lucide-react';\n152: \n153: // RBAC route access map — populate from your PRD.\n154: // Use your project's Role enum. Both sides are stringified at compare time to\n155: // defend against number-vs-string drift between the JWT payload and the enum.\n156: const routeAccess: Record<string, Array<string | number>> = {\n157:   '/dashboard': ['admin', 'user'],\n158:   '/users': ['admin'],\n159:   '/items': ['admin', 'user'],\n160:   '/settings': ['admin'],\n161:   '/profile': ['admin', 'user'],\n162:   // Add routes and allowed roles from your PRD\n163: };\n164: \n165: export default function ProtectedLayout() {\n166:   const { isAuthenticated, authChecked, user } = useAuth();\n167:   const location = useLocation();\n168: \n169:   // 1. Loading state — prevent flash of wrong content\n170:   if (!authChecked) {\n171:     return (\n172:       <div className=\"flex h-screen items-center justify-center\">\n173:         <Loader2 className=\"h-8 w-8 animate-spin text-primary\" />\n174:       </div>\n175:     );\n176:   }\n177: \n178:   // 2. Auth check — redirect to login if not authenticated\n179:   if (!isAuthenticated || !user) {\n180:     return <Navigate to=\"/login\" replace />;\n181:   }\n182: \n183:   // 3. RBAC check — verify user role has access to current route.\n184:   // Stringify both sides to avoid number-vs-string drift (see Role Contract).\n185:   const currentPath = '/' + location.pathname.split('/').filter(Boolean)[0];\n186:   const allowedRoles = routeAccess[currentPath];\n187:   if (allowedRoles && !allowedRoles.map(String).includes(String(user.role))) {\n188:     return <Navigate to=\"/unauthorized\" replace />;\n189:   }\n190: \n191:   // 4. Render layout with protected content\n192:   return (\n193:     <div className=\"flex h-screen\">\n194:       <Sidebar />\n195:       <div className=\"flex-1 flex flex-col min-h-0 overflow-hidden\">\n196:         <Header />\n197:         <main className=\"flex-1 overflow-y-auto p-4 md:p-6\">\n198:           <Outlet />\n199:         </main>\n200:       </div>\n201:     </div>\n202:   );\n203: }\n204: ```\n205: \n206: ### Auth Layout (Guest-Only)\n207: \n208: ```typescript\n209: // ~/pages/auth/layout.tsx\n210: import { GuestGuard } from '~/components/guards/GuestGuard';\n211: \n212: export default function AuthLayout() {\n213:   return <GuestGuard />;\n214: }\n215: ```\n216: \n217: > The auth layout delegates entirely to `GuestGuard`, which handles loading, redirect, and renders `<Outlet />` for guest users.\n218: \n219: ---\n220: \n221: ## Guard Decision Matrix\n222: \n223: | Route Type | Protection Method | `!authChecked` | `!isAuthenticated` | Wrong Role |\n224: |------------|-------------------|----------------|--------------------|-----------|\n225: | Public (/, /about) | None | N/A | N/A | N/A |\n226: | Auth (/login, /signup) | `GuestGuard` in auth layout | Spinner | Allow | N/A |\n227: | Protected (/dashboard/*) | Inline in `ProtectedLayout` | Spinner | → /login | → /unauthorized |\n228: \n229: ---\n230: \n231: ## Auth State Hook\n232: \n233: Guards depend on a `useAuth()` hook that abstracts the auth state source (Redux or Context):\n234: \n235: ```typescript\n236: // ~/hooks/useAuth.ts\n237: import type { AuthState } from '~/types/auth';\n238: \n239: // Implementation: connect to your auth store (Redux or Context)\n240: export function useAuth(): AuthState {\n241:   // Option A: Redux\n242:   // const { user, isAuthenticated, authChecked } = useSelector((state: RootState) => state.auth);\n243: \n244:   // Option B: Context\n245:   // const { user, isAuthenticated, authChecked } = useContext(AuthContext);\n246: \n247:   return { user, isAuthenticated, authChecked };\n248: }\n249: ```\n250: \n251: ### Key State Flags\n252: \n253: - **authChecked**: Set to `true` after initial auth check completes (success or failure). Prevents premature redirects.\n254: - **isAuthenticated**: `true` when user is logged in\n255: - **user**: Contains user object with `role` field for RBAC\n256: \n257: ---\n258: \n259: ## When to Use Standalone Guards vs Inline Layout\n260: \n261: | Scenario | Approach |\n262: |----------|----------|\n263: | Entire route group needs auth + RBAC | **Inline in layout** (recommended) |\n264: | Auth pages (login, signup) | **GuestGuard** as layout |\n265: | One-off route needing extra role check | **RoleGuard** wrapping page content |\n266: | Component-level permission check | **RoleGuard** wrapping specific UI section |\n267: \n268: ---\n269: \n270: ## Best Practices\n271: \n272: ### DO\n273: \n274: - Use inline auth + RBAC checks in layout components (single responsibility)\n275: - Show loading spinner during auth check (prevent flash of content)\n276: - Use `replace: true` on `<Navigate>` to prevent back-button issues\n277: - Check auth BEFORE checking role\n278: - Use the `authChecked` flag to prevent premature redirects\n279: - Define `routeAccess` map from your PRD's role definitions\n280: \n281: ### DON'T\n282: \n283: - Guard every individual page component separately\n284: - Skip loading state (causes flash of wrong content)\n285: - Redirect without `replace` (creates broken history)\n286: - Check role without checking authentication first\n287: - Hardcode role names — derive from your project's PRD/enums\n288: \n289: ---\n290: \n291: ## Implementation Checklist\n292: \n293: When implementing auth guards:\n294: \n295: 1. [ ] `useAuth()` hook created (connecting to Redux or Context)\n296: 2. [ ] `GuestGuard` component created (renders `<Outlet />`)\n297: 3. [ ] `AuthGuard` component created (for one-off use)\n298: 4. [ ] `RoleGuard` component created (for one-off use)\n299: 5. [ ] `ProtectedLayout` has inline auth + RBAC with `routeAccess` map\n300: 6. [ ] Auth layout uses `<GuestGuard />` as its content\n301: 7. [ ] `authChecked` flag set after initial auth check\n302: 8. [ ] Loading spinner shown during auth check\n303: 9. [ ] Redirects use `replace: true`\n304: 10. [ ] `/unauthorized` page exists for role mismatch\n305: \n306: ---\n307: \n308: ## Related Files\n309: \n310: - [routing-guide.md](./routing-guide.md) — Route configuration patterns\n311: - [authentication-architecture.md](./authentication-architecture.md) — Auth flow and state management\n312: - [file-organization.md](./file-organization.md) — Directory structure\n313: - `~/components/guards/GuestGuard.tsx` — Guest guard (renders Outlet)\n314: - `~/components/guards/AuthGuard.tsx` — Auth guard\n315: - `~/components/guards/RoleGuard.tsx` — Role guard\n316: - `~/components/layouts/ProtectedLayout.tsx` — Protected layout with inline RBAC\n317: - `~/hooks/useAuth.ts` — Auth state hook\n\n(End of file - total 317 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Authentication Guards\n\n## Overview\n\nRoute protection using 3 separate guard components and layout-level RBAC. Guards enforce authentication and role-based access control across route trees.\n\n> **Important:** The specific auth method (httpOnly cookies, Bearer tokens, sessions) and role names come from your project's PRD. This guide covers the structural patterns only.\n\n---\n\n## Role Contract (CRITICAL)\n\nYour auth system MUST be internally consistent about the type of `role` on the user object:\n\n- **Either** role is always a `number` (recommended for numeric enums), OR\n- role is always a `string` (recommended for string enums)\n\n**Never mix.** The JWT payload, the `/auth/login` response, the `/users/me` response, and the frontend `AuthUser` type must all agree. If they don't, `allowedRoles.includes(user.role)` fails silently and guards become permissive — a low-privilege user ends up able to view admin pages because `\"1\" !== 1` (or vice versa).\n\nSigns of role-type drift:","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".claude/react/docs/auth-guards.md","time":{"start":1779191438667,"end":1779191438945}},"id":"prt_e4012d8b5001dPX8BZ3JsTt2Rf","sessionID":"ses_1bff4e2c5ffelBqOnmJS1wuf2p","messageID":"msg_e4012ad7d001Ne9hiRmPEHBmqc"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779191440469,"sessionID":"ses_1bff4e2c5ffelBqOnmJS1wuf2p","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_01_KMDguVvFhaeWr6F6bhDb6328","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/react/docs/routing-guide.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/react/docs/routing-guide.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Routing Guide\n2: \n3: React Router 7 implementation with declarative routing and layout-based organization.\n4: \n5: ---\n6: \n7: ## React Router 7 Overview\n8: \n9: The project uses **React Router 7** with:\n10: \n11: - Declarative route configuration\n12: - Layout-based route organization\n13: - Server-side rendering (SSR) enabled\n14: - Type-safe navigation\n15: \n16: ---\n17: \n18: ## Configuration Files\n19: \n20: ### Main Route Configuration\n21: \n22: Location: `~/routes.ts`\n23: \n24: ```typescript\n25: import { type RouteConfig, layout, index, route } from '@react-router/dev/routes';\n26: import { authRoutes } from './routes/auth.routes';\n27: import { protectedRoutes } from './routes/protected.routes';\n28: \n29: export default [\n30:   index('pages/redirect-home.tsx'),\n31:   layout('pages/auth/layout.tsx', authRoutes),\n32:   protectedRoutes,\n33:   route('*', 'pages/not-found.tsx'),\n34: ] satisfies RouteConfig;\n35: ```\n36: \n37: > **Note:** `protectedRoutes` is a single `RouteConfigEntry` (not spread), because it wraps all protected routes with a layout that includes auth + RBAC checks. Add additional route groups (e.g., public routes) as separate `layout()` entries as needed.\n38: \n39: ### React Router Configuration\n40: \n41: Location: `frontend/react-router.config.ts`\n42: \n43: ```typescript\n44: import type { Config } from '@react-router/dev/config';\n45: \n46: export default {\n47:   // Server-side render by default, to enable SPA mode set this to `false`\n48:   ssr: true,\n49: } satisfies Config;\n50: ```\n51: \n52: ---\n53: \n54: ## Route Definitions\n55: \n56: ### Public Routes\n57: \n58: Location: `~/routes/public.routes.ts`\n59: \n60: ```typescript\n61: import { route, index } from '@react-router/dev/routes';\n62: \n63: export const publicRoutes = [\n64:   index('pages/home.tsx'),\n65:   route('about', 'pages/public/about.tsx'),\n66: ];\n67: ```\n68: \n69: ### Auth Routes\n70: \n71: Location: `~/routes/auth.routes.ts`\n72: \n73: ```typescript\n74: import { route } from '@react-router/dev/routes';\n75: \n76: export const authRoutes = [\n77:   route('login', 'pages/auth/login.tsx'),\n78:   route('forgot-password', 'pages/auth/forgot-password.tsx'),\n79: ];\n80: ```\n81: \n82: ### Protected Routes\n83: \n84: Location: `~/routes/protected.routes.ts`\n85: \n86: ```typescript\n87: import { type RouteConfigEntry, route, layout } from '@react-router/dev/routes';\n88: \n89: export const protectedRoutes: RouteConfigEntry = layout('components/layouts/ProtectedLayout.tsx', [\n90:   route('dashboard', 'pages/protected/dashboard.tsx'),\n91:   route('users', 'pages/protected/users.tsx'),\n92:   route('users/:id', 'pages/protected/user-detail.tsx'),\n93:   route('items', 'pages/protected/items.tsx'),\n94:   route('items/new', 'pages/protected/item-form.tsx', { id: 'item-create' }),\n95:   route('items/:id', 'pages/protected/item-detail.tsx'),\n96:   route('items/:id/edit', 'pages/protected/item-form.tsx', { id: 'item-edit' }),\n97:   route('settings', 'pages/protected/settings.tsx'),\n98:   route('profile', 'pages/protected/profile.tsx'),\n99:   route('unauthorized', 'pages/unauthorized.tsx'),\n100:   // Add routes from your PRD here\n101: ]);\n102: ```\n103: \n104: > **Route IDs:** When multiple routes share the same component (e.g., create/edit forms), use the `{ id: 'unique-id' }` option to distinguish them. Access via `useMatches()` or route params.\n105: \n106: ---\n107: \n108: ## Route Helpers\n109: \n110: ### Available Functions\n111: \n112: ```typescript\n113: import { type RouteConfig, type RouteConfigEntry, route, index, layout } from '@react-router/dev/routes';\n114: \n115: // index - Home route for a path\n116: index('pages/home.tsx')  // Renders at parent path\n117: \n118: // route - Named route\n119: route('about', 'pages/about.tsx')  // /about\n120: \n121: // route - With unique ID (for shared components)\n122: route('items/new', 'pages/protected/item-form.tsx', { id: 'item-create' })\n123: route('items/:id/edit', 'pages/protected/item-form.tsx', { id: 'item-edit' })\n124: \n125: // layout - Wraps child routes with a layout component\n126: layout('pages/layout.tsx', childRoutes)\n127: ```\n128: \n129: ### Types\n130: \n131: ```typescript\n132: // RouteConfig - Array of route entries (used for the default export)\n133: export default [...] satisfies RouteConfig;\n134: \n135: // RouteConfigEntry - Single route entry (used for grouped route objects)\n136: export const protectedRoutes: RouteConfigEntry = layout('...', [...]);\n137: ```\n138: \n139: ### Route with Parameters\n140: \n141: ```typescript\n142: // Dynamic route parameter\n143: route('users/:id', 'pages/users/detail.tsx')  // /users/123\n144: \n145: // Optional parameter\n146: route('posts/:id?', 'pages/posts/index.tsx')  // /posts or /posts/123\n147: \n148: // Catch-all\n149: route('*', 'pages/not-found.tsx')  // Any unmatched route\n150: ```\n151: \n152: ---\n153: \n154: ## Layout Components\n155: \n156: ### Auth Layout (Guest-Only)\n157: \n158: Location: `~/pages/auth/layout.tsx`\n159: \n160: ```typescript\n161: import { GuestGuard } from '~/components/guards/GuestGuard';\n162: \n163: export default function AuthLayout() {\n164:   return <GuestGuard />;\n165: }\n166: ```\n167: \n168: > Auth layout delegates entirely to `GuestGuard`, which renders `<Outlet />` for unauthenticated users and redirects authenticated users to their home route.\n169: \n170: ### Protected Layout (Auth + RBAC)\n171: \n172: Location: `~/components/layouts/ProtectedLayout.tsx`\n173: \n174: ```typescript\n175: import { Outlet, Navigate, useLocation } from 'react-router';\n176: import { useAuth } from '~/hooks/useAuth';\n177: import { Sidebar } from '~/components/layout/Sidebar';\n178: import Header from '~/components/layout/Header';\n179: import { Loader2 } from 'lucide-react';\n180: \n181: // RBAC route access map: define which roles can access which routes\n182: // Populate from your PRD's role definitions\n183: const routeAccess: Record<string, string[]> = {\n184:   '/dashboard': ['admin', 'user'],\n185:   '/users': ['admin'],\n186:   '/items': ['admin', 'user'],\n187:   '/settings': ['admin'],\n188:   '/profile': ['admin', 'user'],\n189:   // Add routes and allowed roles from your PRD\n190: };\n191: \n192: export default function ProtectedLayout() {\n193:   const { isAuthenticated, authChecked, user } = useAuth();\n194:   const location = useLocation();\n195: \n196:   if (!authChecked) {\n197:     return (\n198:       <div className=\"flex h-screen items-center justify-center\">\n199:         <Loader2 className=\"h-8 w-8 animate-spin text-primary\" />\n200:       </div>\n201:     );\n202:   }\n203: \n204:   if (!isAuthenticated || !user) {\n205:     return <Navigate to=\"/login\" replace />;\n206:   }\n207: \n208:   // RBAC check: verify user role has access to current route\n209:   const currentPath = '/' + location.pathname.split('/').filter(Boolean)[0];\n210:   const allowedRoles = routeAccess[currentPath];\n211:   if (allowedRoles && !allowedRoles.includes(user.role)) {\n212:     return <Navigate to=\"/unauthorized\" replace />;\n213:   }\n214: \n215:   return (\n216:     <div className=\"flex h-screen\">\n217:       <Sidebar />\n218:       <div className=\"flex-1 flex flex-col min-h-0 overflow-hidden\">\n219:         <Header />\n220:         <main className=\"flex-1 overflow-y-auto p-4 md:p-6\">\n221:           <Outlet />\n222:         </main>\n223:       </div>\n224:     </div>\n225:   );\n226: }\n227: ```\n228: \n229: > **Key pattern:** Auth check + RBAC check are **inline** in the layout component. No separate guard wrapper needed — the layout itself acts as the guard.\n230: \n231: ### Redirect Home Page\n232: \n233: Location: `~/pages/redirect-home.tsx`\n234: \n235: **SSR mode** (ssr: true):\n236: \n237: ```typescript\n238: import { redirect } from 'react-router';\n239: import type { Route } from './+types/redirect-home';\n240: \n241: export function loader(_: Route.LoaderArgs) {\n242:   return redirect('/login');\n243: }\n244: \n245: export default function RedirectHome() {\n246:   return null;\n247: }\n248: ```\n249: \n250: > Uses React Router 7's `loader()` function for server-side redirect at the root path (`/`). Change the target to your project's default route.\n251: \n252: **SPA mode** (ssr: false):\n253: \n254: ```typescript\n255: import { Navigate } from 'react-router';\n256: import { useAuth } from '~/hooks/useAuth';\n257: \n258: export default function RedirectHome() {\n259:   const { isAuthenticated, isLoading, user } = useAuth();\n260: \n261:   if (isLoading) {\n262:     return <LoadingSpinner />;\n263:   }\n264: \n265:   if (!isAuthenticated) {\n266:     return <Navigate to=\"/login\" replace />;\n267:   }\n268: \n269:   // Redirect to role-specific home\n270:   return <Navigate to={getHomeRouteForRole(user.role)} replace />;\n271: }\n272: ```\n273: \n274: > SPA mode does not support `loader()` exports. Use client-side `<Navigate>` instead.\n275: \n276: ---\n277: \n278: ## Navigation\n279: \n280: ### Link Component\n281: \n282: ```typescript\n283: import { Link } from 'react-router';\n284: \n285: // Basic link\n286: <Link to=\"/about\">About</Link>\n287: \n288: // With classes\n289: <Link to=\"/dashboard\" className=\"text-primary hover:underline\">\n290:   Dashboard\n291: </Link>\n292: \n293: // External link (use anchor)\n294: <a href=\"https://example.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">\n295:   External\n296: </a>\n297: ```\n298: \n299: ### Programmatic Navigation\n300: \n301: ```typescript\n302: import { useNavigate } from 'react-router';\n303: \n304: export default function MyComponent() {\n305:   const navigate = useNavigate();\n306: \n307:   const handleClick = () => {\n308:     // Navigate to route\n309:     navigate('/dashboard');\n310: \n311:     // Navigate with replace (no history entry)\n312:     navigate('/login', { replace: true });\n313: \n314:     // Go back\n315:     navigate(-1);\n316:   };\n317: \n318:   return <button onClick={handleClick}>Navigate</button>;\n319: }\n320: ```\n321: \n322: ### Using Button with Link (asChild)\n323: \n324: ```typescript\n325: import { Button } from '~/components/ui/button';\n326: import { Link } from 'react-router';\n327: \n328: <Button asChild>\n329:   <Link to=\"/dashboard\">Go to Dashboard</Link>\n330: </Button>\n331: ```\n332: \n333: ---\n334: \n335: ## Route Parameters\n336: \n337: ### Accessing Parameters\n338: \n339: ```typescript\n340: import { useParams } from 'react-router';\n341: \n342: export default function UserDetail() {\n343:   const { id } = useParams<{ id: string }>();\n344: \n345:   return <div>User ID: {id}</div>;\n346: }\n347: ```\n348: \n349: ### Search Parameters\n350: \n351: ```typescript\n352: import { useSearchParams } from 'react-router';\n353: \n354: export default function SearchPage() {\n355:   const [searchParams, setSearchParams] = useSearchParams();\n356: \n357:   const query = searchParams.get('q') || '';\n358:   const page = searchParams.get('page') || '1';\n359: \n360:   const updateSearch = (newQuery: string) => {\n361:     setSearchParams({ q: newQuery, page: '1' });\n362:   };\n363: \n364:   return (\n365:     <input\n366:       value={query}\n367:       onChange={(e) => updateSearch(e.target.value)}\n368:     />\n369:   );\n370: }\n371: ```\n372: \n373: ---\n374: \n375: ## Route Organization\n376: \n377: ### Adding a New Route to Protected Area\n378: \n379: 1. Add the route definition to `~/routes/protected.routes.ts`:\n380: \n381: ```typescript\n382: // Add to the existing protectedRoutes layout array\n383: route('reports', 'pages/protected/reports.tsx'),\n384: route('reports/:id', 'pages/protected/report-detail.tsx'),\n385: ```\n386: \n387: 2. Create the page component:\n388: \n389: ```typescript\n390: // ~/pages/protected/reports.tsx\n391: export default function ReportsPage() {\n392:   return <div>Reports</div>;\n393: }\n394: ```\n395: \n396: 3. Add RBAC entry in `ProtectedLayout.tsx`:\n397: \n398: ```typescript\n399: const routeAccess: Record<string, string[]> = {\n400:   // ... existing routes\n401:   '/reports': ['admin', 'manager'],\n402: };\n403: ```\n404: \n405: ### Adding a New Route Group (e.g., Public Routes)\n406: \n407: 1. Create route definitions file:\n408: \n409: ```typescript\n410: // ~/routes/public.routes.ts\n411: import { route, index } from '@react-router/dev/routes';\n412: \n413: export const publicRoutes = [\n414:   index('pages/home.tsx'),\n415:   route('about', 'pages/public/about.tsx'),\n416: ];\n417: ```\n418: \n419: 2. Add to main routes:\n420: \n421: ```typescript\n422: // ~/routes.ts\n423: import { publicRoutes } from './routes/public.routes';\n424: \n425: export default [\n426:   index('pages/redirect-home.tsx'),\n427:   layout('pages/layout.tsx', publicRoutes),\n428:   layout('pages/auth/layout.tsx', authRoutes),\n429:   protectedRoutes,\n430: ] satisfies RouteConfig;\n431: ```\n432: \n433: ---\n434: \n435: ## Summary\n436: \n437: **Routing Checklist:**\n438: \n439: - ✅ Define routes in `routes/*.routes.ts` files\n440: - ✅ Use `RouteConfigEntry` for protected route groups with `layout()` wrapper\n441: - ✅ Use `route()` for named routes, `index()` for default routes\n442: - ✅ Use route IDs (`{ id: 'name' }`) when sharing components across routes\n443: - ✅ Use `redirect-home.tsx` with `loader()` (SSR) or `<Navigate>` (SPA) for root redirect\n444: - ✅ Auth + RBAC checks inline in protected layout (not separate guard wrappers)\n445: - ✅ `routeAccess` map for per-route role checking\n446: - ✅ Auth layout delegates to `GuestGuard` for guest-only pages\n447: - ✅ Use `Link` for navigation (not `<a>`)\n448: - ✅ Use `useNavigate` for programmatic navigation\n449: - ✅ Use `useParams` for route parameters\n450: - ✅ Add route files to main `routes.ts`\n451: \n452: **See Also:**\n453: \n454: - [auth-guards.md](auth-guards.md) - Auth guard patterns\n455: - [file-organization.md](file-organization.md) - Route file structure\n456: - [common-patterns.md](common-patterns.md) - Auth patterns\n457: - [complete-examples.md](complete-examples.md) - Full routing examples\n\n(End of file - total 457 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Routing Guide\n\nReact Router 7 implementation with declarative routing and layout-based organization.\n\n---\n\n## React Router 7 Overview\n\nThe project uses **React Router 7** with:\n\n- Declarative route configuration\n- Layout-based route organization\n- Server-side rendering (SSR) enabled\n- Type-safe navigation\n\n---\n\n## Configuration Files\n\n### Main Route Configuration","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".claude/react/docs/routing-guide.md","time":{"start":1779191440193,"end":1779191440468}},"id":"prt_e4012de99001Sudayt4QjcIVst","sessionID":"ses_1bff4e2c5ffelBqOnmJS1wuf2p","messageID":"msg_e4012ad7d001Ne9hiRmPEHBmqc"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779191441999,"sessionID":"ses_1bff4e2c5ffelBqOnmJS1wuf2p","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_02_MaySuucSHJPKG7xPvvtV9113","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/react/docs/i18n-architecture.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/react/docs/i18n-architecture.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # i18n Architecture Guide\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: When a project requires multilingual support, use `react-i18next` for internationalization.\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Setup\n10: \n11: ### 1. Install Dependencies\n12: \n13: ```bash\n14: npm install react-i18next i18next i18next-http-backend i18next-browser-languagedetector\n15: ```\n16: \n17: ### 2. Create i18n Configuration\n18: \n19: ```typescript\n20: // app/i18n.ts\n21: import i18n from 'i18next';\n22: import { initReactI18next } from 'react-i18next';\n23: import LanguageDetector from 'i18next-browser-languagedetector';\n24: import Backend from 'i18next-http-backend';\n25: \n26: i18n\n27:   .use(Backend)\n28:   .use(LanguageDetector)\n29:   .use(initReactI18next)\n30:   .init({\n31:     fallbackLng: 'en',\n32:     supportedLngs: ['en', 'ko'],\n33:     defaultNS: 'translation',\n34:     interpolation: {\n35:       escapeValue: false, // React already escapes\n36:     },\n37:     backend: {\n38:       loadPath: '/locales/{{lng}}/{{ns}}.json',\n39:     },\n40:   });\n41: \n42: export default i18n;\n43: ```\n44: \n45: ### 3. Create Locale Files\n46: \n47: ```\n48: public/\n49: └── locales/\n50:     ├── en/\n51:     │   └── translation.json\n52:     └── ko/\n53:         └── translation.json\n54: ```\n55: \n56: ```json\n57: // public/locales/en/translation.json\n58: {\n59:   \"common\": {\n60:     \"save\": \"Save\",\n61:     \"cancel\": \"Cancel\",\n62:     \"delete\": \"Delete\",\n63:     \"loading\": \"Loading...\",\n64:     \"noResults\": \"No results found\",\n65:     \"error\": \"Something went wrong\"\n66:   },\n67:   \"auth\": {\n68:     \"login\": \"Login\",\n69:     \"logout\": \"Logout\",\n70:     \"email\": \"Email\",\n71:     \"password\": \"Password\"\n72:   }\n73: }\n74: ```\n75: \n76: ### 4. Initialize in Entry Point\n77: \n78: ```typescript\n79: // root.tsx\n80: import './i18n';\n81: ```\n82: \n83: ---\n84: \n85: ## Usage in Components\n86: \n87: ### Basic Translation\n88: \n89: ```typescript\n90: import { useTranslation } from 'react-i18next';\n91: \n92: export const SaveButton = () => {\n93:   const { t } = useTranslation();\n94:   return <button>{t('common.save')}</button>;\n95: };\n96: ```\n97: \n98: ### With Variables\n99: \n100: ```typescript\n101: // translation.json: \"welcome\": \"Hello, {{name}}!\"\n102: <p>{t('welcome', { name: user.name })}</p>\n103: ```\n104: \n105: ### Plurals\n106: \n107: ```typescript\n108: // translation.json: \"items_one\": \"{{count}} item\", \"items_other\": \"{{count}} items\"\n109: <span>{t('items', { count: itemCount })}</span>\n110: ```\n111: \n112: ---\n113: \n114: ## Language Switcher\n115: \n116: ```typescript\n117: import { useTranslation } from 'react-i18next';\n118: \n119: export const LanguageSwitcher = () => {\n120:   const { i18n } = useTranslation();\n121: \n122:   return (\n123:     <select\n124:       value={i18n.language}\n125:       onChange={(e) => i18n.changeLanguage(e.target.value)}\n126:     >\n127:       <option value=\"en\">English</option>\n128:       <option value=\"ko\">한국어</option>\n129:     </select>\n130:   );\n131: };\n132: ```\n133: \n134: ---\n135: \n136: ## MANDATORY Rules\n137: \n138: - **Every visible string** in UI components MUST use `t()` — no hardcoded text\n139: - **Locale files** must exist for ALL supported languages before shipping\n140: - **Keys** use dot notation organized by feature: `auth.login`, `dashboard.title`\n141: - **Fallback language** must always be set (typically `en`)\n142: - **Do NOT** use string concatenation for translated strings — use interpolation variables\n143: - **Form validation messages** should also be translated via Zod `.refine()` with `t()`\n144: \n145: ## E2E Testing with i18n\n146: \n147: When writing Playwright tests for i18n apps:\n148: - Use `[data-testid]` selectors (language-independent) — preferred\n149: - Or bilingual regex: `button:has-text(/Save|저장/i)`\n150: - NEVER use English-only text selectors when default locale is not English\n151: \n152: ---\n153: \n154: ## Related\n155: \n156: - [best-practices.md](best-practices.md) — Coding standards\n157: - [component-patterns.md](component-patterns.md) — Component structure\n158: - [typescript-standards.md](typescript-standards.md) — Type safety\n\n(End of file - total 158 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# i18n Architecture Guide\n\n## Overview\n\nWhen a project requires multilingual support, use `react-i18next` for internationalization.\n\n---\n\n## Setup\n\n### 1. Install Dependencies\n\n```bash\nnpm install react-i18next i18next i18next-http-backend i18next-browser-languagedetector\n```\n\n### 2. Create i18n Configuration\n\n```typescript\n// app/i18n.ts","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".claude/react/docs/i18n-architecture.md","time":{"start":1779191441721,"end":1779191441998}},"id":"prt_e4012e46c001QH2PozDUdIMgr9","sessionID":"ses_1bff4e2c5ffelBqOnmJS1wuf2p","messageID":"msg_e4012ad7d001Ne9hiRmPEHBmqc"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779191443580,"sessionID":"ses_1bff4e2c5ffelBqOnmJS1wuf2p","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_03_qEXMLJgnflBZJbUZHITW5601","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/react/docs/authentication-architecture.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/react/docs/authentication-architecture.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Authentication Architecture\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: Common authentication architecture patterns for frontend applications. The specific auth strategy (cookies, tokens, sessions) should be determined by your project's PRD.\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Security Model\n10: \n11: ### Auth Strategy Comparison\n12: \n13: | Storage Method | XSS Vulnerable | CSRF Vulnerable | Notes |\n14: |----------------|----------------|-----------------|-------|\n15: | localStorage | YES | No | Simple but risky — tokens accessible to JS |\n16: | sessionStorage | YES | No | Cleared on tab close, still XSS-vulnerable |\n17: | httpOnly Cookie | No | Possible (mitigated) | Secure — JS cannot access tokens |\n18: | In-memory (variable) | No | No | Lost on refresh — must combine with refresh strategy |\n19: \n20: ### Common Cookie Configuration (when using httpOnly cookies)\n21: \n22: ```\n23: httpOnly: true      # JavaScript cannot access\n24: secure: true        # HTTPS only (production)\n25: sameSite: 'strict'  # Or 'lax'/'none' depending on cross-origin needs\n26: ```\n27: \n28: ---\n29: \n30: ## Authentication Flow\n31: \n32: ### React Router 7 Framework Mode Flow\n33: \n34: ```\n35: root.tsx (App shell)\n36:     |\n37: AuthProvider wraps entire app\n38:     |\n39: On mount: AuthInitializer validates session (cookie/token)\n40:     |\n41: Sets authChecked: true (success or failure)\n42:     |\n43: Route renders:\n44:     ├── Auth pages → GuestGuard (renders <Outlet />) → redirects if authenticated\n45:     └── Protected pages → ProtectedLayout (inline RBAC) → checks auth + role\n46: ```\n47: \n48: ### Login Flow\n49: \n50: ```\n51: User submits credentials\n52:     |\n53: POST /auth/login (credentials)\n54:     |\n55: Backend validates → sets httpOnly cookie (or returns token)\n56:     |\n57: Frontend receives user data\n58:     |\n59: Update auth state: setUser(user) / dispatch(loginSuccess(user))\n60:     |\n61: Navigate to getHomeRouteForRole(user.role)\n62: ```\n63: \n64: ### App Load / Refresh Flow\n65: \n66: ```\n67: App loads → AuthInitializer / AuthProvider runs\n68:     |\n69: Validate session: POST /auth/refresh (or GET /auth/profile)\n70:     |\n71: ├── Valid → restore user state, set authChecked: true\n72: └── Invalid → clear local state, set authChecked: true\n73:     |\n74: ProtectedLayout makes routing decisions (inline auth + RBAC check)\n75: ```\n76: \n77: ---\n78: \n79: ## Role-Based Access Control\n80: \n81: ### Pattern\n82: \n83: | Role | Dashboard Route | Description |\n84: |------|----------------|-------------|\n85: | ADMIN | /admin | Administrative access |\n86: | USER | /dashboard | Standard user access |\n87: | *Your roles* | *Your routes* | *Defined in your PRD* |\n88: \n89: ### Route Protection\n90: \n91: | Route Pattern | Guard | Behavior |\n92: |---------------|-------|----------|\n93: | `/`, `/login`, `/signup` | `guestOnly` | Redirect logged-in users to home |\n94: | `/admin/*` | `requiredRole=\"admin\"` | Require admin role |\n95: | `/dashboard/*` | `requiredRole=\"user\"` | Require user role |\n96: \n97: > **Note:** Replace role names and routes with your project's actual roles from the PRD.\n98: \n99: ---\n100: \n101: ## Key Components\n102: \n103: ### 1. ProtectedLayout (Inline RBAC — Recommended)\n104: \n105: Auth + RBAC checks are inline in the layout component. The layout itself acts as the guard:\n106: \n107: ```typescript\n108: // ~/components/layouts/ProtectedLayout.tsx\n109: const routeAccess: Record<string, string[]> = {\n110:   '/dashboard': ['admin', 'user'],\n111:   '/users': ['admin'],\n112:   '/settings': ['admin'],\n113:   // Populate from your PRD's role definitions\n114: };\n115: \n116: export default function ProtectedLayout() {\n117:   const { isAuthenticated, authChecked, user } = useAuth();\n118:   const location = useLocation();\n119: \n120:   if (!authChecked) return <LoadingSpinner />;\n121:   if (!isAuthenticated || !user) return <Navigate to=\"/login\" replace />;\n122: \n123:   const currentPath = '/' + location.pathname.split('/').filter(Boolean)[0];\n124:   const allowedRoles = routeAccess[currentPath];\n125:   if (allowedRoles && !allowedRoles.includes(user.role)) {\n126:     return <Navigate to=\"/unauthorized\" replace />;\n127:   }\n128: \n129:   return <div><Sidebar /><Outlet /></div>;\n130: }\n131: ```\n132: \n133: ### 2. GuestGuard (Auth Pages)\n134: \n135: Renders `<Outlet />` for unauthenticated users, redirects authenticated users:\n136: \n137: ```typescript\n138: export function GuestGuard() {\n139:   const { isAuthenticated, authChecked } = useAuth();\n140:   if (!authChecked) return <LoadingSpinner />;\n141:   if (isAuthenticated) return <Navigate to=\"/dashboard\" replace />;\n142:   return <Outlet />;\n143: }\n144: ```\n145: \n146: ### 3. Auth State (Redux or Context)\n147: \n148: ```typescript\n149: // AuthState is defined in ~/types/auth.d.ts and imported wherever needed:\n150: // - Redux authSlice: import type { AuthState } from '~/types/auth';\n151: // - AuthContext: import type { AuthState } from '~/types/auth';\n152: \n153: // ~/types/auth.d.ts\n154: export interface AuthState {\n155:   user: AuthUser | null;\n156:   isAuthenticated: boolean;\n157:   isLoading: boolean;\n158:   authChecked: boolean;   // true after initial auth check completes\n159:   error: string | null;\n160: }\n161: ```\n162: \n163: ### 4. AuthInitializer / AuthProvider\n164: \n165: Runs on app load to validate session with backend:\n166: \n167: ```typescript\n168: // Context pattern — AuthProvider wraps app in root.tsx\n169: function AuthProvider({ children }) {\n170:   const [user, setUser] = useState(null);\n171:   const [authChecked, setAuthChecked] = useState(false);\n172: \n173:   useEffect(() => {\n174:     api.post('/auth/refresh')\n175:       .then(() => { /* restore user from storage/response */ })\n176:       .catch(() => { /* clear state */ })\n177:       .finally(() => setAuthChecked(true));\n178:   }, []);\n179: \n180:   return <AuthContext.Provider value={{ user, isAuthenticated: !!user, authChecked }}>\n181:     {children}\n182:   </AuthContext.Provider>;\n183: }\n184: ```\n185: \n186: ### 5. Auth Utilities\n187: \n188: ```typescript\n189: mapToAuthUser(backendUser)       // Map API user to AuthUser\n190: getHomeRouteForRole(role)        // Get home route for role\n191: hasRole(userRole, targetRole)    // Check if user has a specific role\n192: ```\n193: \n194: ### 6. Token Refresh with Axios Interceptor\n195: \n196: ```typescript\n197: // 401 interceptor with refresh queue (prevents parallel refresh calls)\n198: api.interceptors.response.use(\n199:   (response) => response,\n200:   async (error) => {\n201:     const originalRequest = error.config;\n202:     if (error.response?.status === 401 && !originalRequest._retry) {\n203:       originalRequest._retry = true;\n204:       try {\n205:         await api.post('/auth/refresh');\n206:         return api(originalRequest);\n207:       } catch {\n208:         // Refresh failed — force logout\n209:         localStorage.removeItem('hasSession');\n210:         window.location.href = '/login';\n211:       }\n212:     }\n213:     return Promise.reject(error);\n214:   },\n215: );\n216: ```\n217: \n218: ---\n219: \n220: ## Troubleshooting\n221: \n222: ### Flash of login page on protected routes\n223: **Cause**: `isInitialized` not checked before routing\n224: **Solution**: Ensure AuthGuard waits for `isInitialized: true`\n225: \n226: ### Infinite redirect loops\n227: **Cause**: Redirect happening on every render\n228: **Solution**: Check current path before redirecting\n229: \n230: ### Auth state not persisting\n231: **Cause**: Session not being validated on app load\n232: **Solution**: Ensure AuthInitializer runs and validates session with backend\n233: \n234: ### Role check failing\n235: **Cause**: Backend returns role in unexpected format (string vs number)\n236: **Solution**: Use a `hasRole()` utility that normalizes and compares\n237: \n238: ---\n239: \n240: ## Implementation Guides\n241: \n242: For detailed implementation patterns, see:\n243: \n244: - [Authentication Patterns](authentication.md) — Login/logout flows, auth state, 401 handling\n245: - [Auth Guards](auth-guards.md) — Guard components, inline RBAC, guard decision matrix\n246: - [Routing Guide](routing-guide.md) — Route configuration, layouts, navigation\n247: - [Common Patterns](common-patterns.md) — Role-based rendering, useAuth hook\n\n(End of file - total 247 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Authentication Architecture\n\n## Overview\n\nCommon authentication architecture patterns for frontend applications. The specific auth strategy (cookies, tokens, sessions) should be determined by your project's PRD.\n\n---\n\n## Security Model\n\n### Auth Strategy Comparison\n\n| Storage Method | XSS Vulnerable | CSRF Vulnerable | Notes |\n|----------------|----------------|-----------------|-------|\n| localStorage | YES | No | Simple but risky — tokens accessible to JS |\n| sessionStorage | YES | No | Cleared on tab close, still XSS-vulnerable |\n| httpOnly Cookie | No | Possible (mitigated) | Secure — JS cannot access tokens |\n| In-memory (variable) | No | No | Lost on refresh — must combine with refresh strategy |\n\n### Common Cookie Configuration (when using httpOnly cookies)","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".claude/react/docs/authentication-architecture.md","time":{"start":1779191443300,"end":1779191443578}},"id":"prt_e4012ea93001nAguJ51xxwRfTh","sessionID":"ses_1bff4e2c5ffelBqOnmJS1wuf2p","messageID":"msg_e4012ad7d001Ne9hiRmPEHBmqc"}}
